<h1>NOMINEE RIDER (SAFE Edition)</h1>

<p>
This Nominee Rider (this <strong>“Rider”</strong>) is attached to and made part of the
SAFE (the <strong>“SAFE”</strong>) dated _____________ by and between
_________________________ (<strong>“Company”</strong>) and
_________________________, a ________ LLC (the <strong>“Nominee”</strong>).
</p>

<h2>1. Purpose and Beneficial Ownership</h2>
<p>The parties acknowledge and agree that:</p>
<ul>
  <li>The Nominee is entering into the SAFE solely as the record holder and nominee on behalf of its members (the <strong>“Beneficial Owners”</strong>).</li>
  <li>The Nominee does not possess any beneficial or economic ownership interest in the SAFE or any resulting securities except as agent for the Beneficial Owners.</li>
  <li>All economic and beneficial ownership rights are held indirectly by the Beneficial Owners through the Nominee.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. Appointment of Nominee Delegate</h2>
<p>
The Beneficial Owners hereby appoint:
</p>
<p>
<strong>Nominee Delegate:</strong> _________________________________
</p>
<p>
The Nominee Delegate acts as the authorized representative and limited attorney-in-fact of the Nominee solely in connection with the SAFE.
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Acts as the primary point of contact for the Company</li>
  <li>Communicates with the Company on behalf of the Nominee</li>
  <li>Executes instructions, consents, and administrative actions</li>
</ul>

<p>
The Nominee Delegate is not a Beneficial Owner by virtue of this role unless separately holding membership interest.
</p>

<h2>3. Limited Power of Attorney</h2>
<p>The Nominee grants the Nominee Delegate a limited, revocable power of attorney to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Receive notices and communications from the Company</li>
  <li>Provide voting directions, waivers, and consents as permitted under the SAFE</li>
  <li>Execute documents related to amendments, conversions, or administrative matters</li>
  <li>Take ministerial actions necessary to preserve SAFE rights</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Duty to Consult</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Use best efforts to consult Beneficial Owners prior to discretionary decisions</li>
  <li>Act in accordance with majority-expressed wishes</li>
  <li>Maintain reasonable records of instructions or votes</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Economic Rights</h2>
<p>
All economic benefits, including equity, distributions, or proceeds, shall be received by the Nominee and distributed proportionately to the Beneficial Owners in accordance with the operating agreement.
</p>

<h2>6. Voting and Consent Rights</h2>
<p>
Unless otherwise required by law or the Company:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Voting rights shall be exercised per Beneficial Owner instructions (majority vote by default)</li>
  <li>If instructions are not timely received, the Nominee Delegate may act in good-faith administrative discretion</li>
</ul>

<h2>7. Limitations on Authority</h2>
<p>Neither the Nominee nor Nominee Delegate may, without Beneficial Owner approval:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Transfer or assign the SAFE</li>
  <li>Pledge or encumber the SAFE</li>
  <li>Modify ownership or economic allocations</li>
  <li>Amend this Rider except as permitted herein</li>
</ul>

<h2>8. Replacement of Nominee Delegate</h2>
<p>
Beneficial Owners may appoint or remove a Nominee Delegate by majority vote. Replacement becomes effective upon written notice to the Company.
</p>

<h2>9. Indemnification</h2>
<p>
Beneficial Owners shall indemnify the Nominee and Nominee Delegate for actions taken in good faith, excluding fraud, willful misconduct, or self-dealing.
</p>

<h2>10. Term and Termination</h2>
<p>
This Rider terminates upon transfer, conversion, dissolution of the Nominee, or vote of Beneficial Owners.
</p>

<h2>11. Company Acknowledgment</h2>
<p>
The Company acknowledges the Nominee as the sole record holder and may rely on communications from the Nominee Delegate.
</p>

<h2>12. Beneficial Owner Protections</h2>
<p>
This Rider does not create personal liability, guarantees, or joint liability among Beneficial Owners.
</p>

<h2>13. Governing Law</h2>
<p>
This Rider shall be governed by the laws of the State of ____________________.
</p>

<h2>14. Miscellaneous</h2>
<ul>
  <li>This Rider controls in case of conflict</li>
  <li>Amendments require majority Beneficial Owner approval</li>
  <li>Electronic signatures are valid</li>
</ul>

<h2>Signatures</h2>

<div class="signature">
<p><strong>Nominee (Investment Club LLC):</strong> Master Series LLC</p>
<p>By: ____________________________</p>
<p>Date: __________________________</p>

<p><strong>Nominee Delegate:</strong></p>
<p>Name: __________________________</p>
<p>Signature: ______________________</p>

<p><strong>Company Acknowledgment (Optional):</strong></p>
<p>Signature: ______________________</p>
</div>

<hr />

<h1>EXHIBIT A – SAFE Decision Matrix</h1>

<h2>Administration & Notices</h2>
<p>Actions the Nominee Delegate may take independently in good faith.</p>

<h2>Majority Vote Actions</h2>
<p>Actions requiring majority approval of Beneficial Owners.</p>

<h2>Supermajority Actions</h2>
<p>Actions requiring ≥66% approval.</p>

<h2>Unanimous Consent Actions</h2>
<p>Actions affecting ownership or economic allocations.</p>

<h2>Emergency Authority</h2>
<p>
Nominee Delegate may act if failure to act would materially harm Beneficial Owners.
</p>

<hr />

<h1>EXHIBIT B – Nominee Delegate Appointment Certificate</h1>

<h2>Appointment</h2>
<p>
The Nominee appoints the Nominee Delegate to act under the SAFE and Nominee Rider.
</p>

<h2>Scope of Authority</h2>
<p>
Limited to administrative and authorized voting actions.
</p>

<h2>Company Reliance</h2>
<p>
The Company may rely on this appointment until revoked.
</p>

<h2>Signatures</h2>
<p>Nominee Signature: __________________________</p>
<p>Nominee Delegate Signature: __________________</p>

